description:
Boomaroo Nurseries’ is a world class vegetable seedling producer, supplying over 300 million seedlings and 1.5 million garden and indoor plants to growers and nurseries across Victoria, New South Wales, Queensland, ACT, Tasmania, and South Australia.
We are looking for a General Nursery Hand to work in our Southbrook Nursery.
Some of tasks could include:
Operate a Forklift;
Spraying insecticides, fungicides, and herbicides;
Assist with Fertigation;
Watering;
Trimming;
Following the production schedule as set out by the Head Grower and Production Manager;
Pricking, moving plants, weeding;
Other general nursery hand duties including loading/unloading, laboring duties & cleaning.
About you:
Be physically fit;
Eye for detail and ability to follow a schedule and instructions;
Forklift license and experience operating or willingness to learn (desirable);
Experience spraying and a chemical users permit (desirable);
Experience operating manufacturing or other heavy equipment (desirable);
Available to work a flexible roster, across weekdays.
organics@boomaroo.com
